EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO ELECTIONS -- MAIL BALLOTS
***
1 This act would require that only the mail ballot voter, their spouse, court appointed
2 guardian, cohabitant, or any adult person related to the voter by blood or marriage, be allowed to
3 physically mail the voted mail ballot. A violation would be a misdemeanor punishable by
4 imprisonment not to exceed one year or a fine not to exceed one thousand dollars ($1,000), or both.
5 This act would take effect upon passage.
